cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.PL 

This paper analyzes the TLS security configurations and certificates of plain-domains and their equivalent www-domains, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the prevalence of this phenomenon in the most-visited domains, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The analysis of datasets and the comparison of TLS configurations could involve statistical inference (cs.SI) and programming languages (cs.PL) for data processing and analysis.
